[Check-out]

table.description:
Our English cottage home located in the heart of Mont Albert/Box Hill is conveniently located only a few minutes from all that the area has to offer. Enjoy the gastronomy of local cafes and restaurants, or head to Box Hill Central nearby for your shopping and entertainment needs.

[Welcome]
Welcome to our English cottage themed home filled with historical charm. Upon entry, a cosy living room welcomes you. The space has been thoughtfully fitted, including a couch that can covert into a sofabed if required. The adjoining dining area can accommodate 6 and is perfect for your entertaining needs. The recently renovated kitchen is equipped with all the essentials you will require for your convenient and comfort. 
The living room has an airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use. We hope you enjoy our home as much as we do! 

[Bedrooms]
Two bedrooms contain queen-sized beds, and the third bedroom has a single-sized bed. Both beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The living room also has a sofabed which can be converted to accommodate the extra guest or two. 

[Sofabed]
Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check-in. Last-minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

[Bathroom]
There are two bathrooms in total and they are both prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcomed to use the iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
The private garage can accommodate 2 cars. If you have additional cars with you, you may park along the street outside the property.

Guests will have access to the entire home and parking is available on-site (a charge applies). 


[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located in the heart Mont Albert, our home is centrally located to offer you all that the area has to offer. Located a mere 5min drive from Box Hill Central, you will find a plethora of dining, shopping and entertainment options a short commute away.

There is a tram stop located outside the home that will take you to Box Hill Central or into the CBD. Mont Albert train station is a short 10min walk away.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the big bins located outside the home.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. 
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Our newly built and luxurious, 2 bedroom apartment, MARCO, will allow you to experience Melbourne at its finest and fullest. Overlook the Albert Park Lake and Sea right from the balcony of this cosy apartment. You will also find yourself near the bustling CBD, Southbank Promenade, Garden and Arts Precinct, and Crown Casino. With easy access to the city via public transport around the area, hurry and make this place your first step in exploring all that Melbourne has to offer.

The apartment is inspired by Scandinavian interior design, with the living room featuring a dining table, TV, coffee table, a cozy sofa and a fully equip open-concept kitchen for you to cook up a meal. Separate from the living room is an open balcony with a gorgeous view. 

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. The request for sofabed will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

Two bedrooms contain beautifully styled Queen bed and Single bed with clean and luxurious linen to keep you comfortable during your stay. Upon arrival, you will also find the bathroom stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo, conditioner, toilet paper and fresh bath towels. A washing machine and dryer is also available for guests to use.

Free WiFi will be available throughout your stay, which will be detailed in the manual provided.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located a short distance away from the city, you will find yourself near the Southbank Promenade, Crown Casino, National Gallery of Victoria, Arts Centre, Queen Victoria Gardens and Sea Life Melbourne Aquarium. There are also multiple restaurant options located near the apartment.

Trams on City Road are located 200m away.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
This two bedroom house located in inner city Albert Park is situated only a block away from the fantastic St. Kilda area beach and Bay. Portraying a classical period exterior with an entirely contemporary interior, this home is the perfect base for professionals, friends, and families. Two bedrooms, each with their own bathroom, complement an invitingly open central living space, large dining/entertaining area , and a well-equipped modern kitchen.

[Welcome]
This recently renovated single-level home located in the heart of Albert Park is your perfect Melbourne bayside getaway. The living room contains designer furnishings with the most comfortable sofa, and the kitchen is fully equipped and has been prepared with all the essential cooking equipment and utensils. The main entertaining space has large floor length glass doors that open up to the deck that bathe the space in warmth. Enjoy your morning coffees/teas or evening wines out on the deck or around the fireplace in the separate sitting room. Central heating and cooling is available throughout the home for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Bedrooms]
The bedrooms each contain a queen bed with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathrooms]
The bathrooms are prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron and washing machine during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Barbeque]
The barbeque will only be made available upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for the barbeque will incur an additional surcharge of $50.

[Carpark]
1 free carpark is also included with your stay.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm.

Enjoy serene village-style living in Albert park surrounded by some of the best cafes, restaurants, bars and beaches in Melbourne. With the beach just minutes walk away, and the city a mere 10 minute drive away, you will never be too far off from the next pleasant surprise that Melbourne has to offer!

Parking is allocated for 1 car, and will also be well serviced by public transport, with tram routes 12, 96 and 1 a few blocks away, which can get you into the city within 15 mins, or in St Kilda (beach) in 10 mins.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.space:
[Welcome]
This recently renovated single-level home located in the heart of Albert Park is your perfect Melbourne bayside getaway. The living room contains designer furnishings with the most comfortable sofa, and the kitchen is fully equipped and has been prepared with all the essential cooking equipment and utensils. The main entertaining space has large floor length glass doors that open up to the deck that bathe the space in warmth. Enjoy your morning coffees/teas or evening wines out on the deck or around the fireplace in the separate sitting room. Central heating and cooling is available throughout the home for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Bedrooms]
The bedrooms each contain a queen bed with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathrooms]
The bathrooms are prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron and washing machine during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Barbeque]
The barbeque will only be made available upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for the barbeque will incur an additional surcharge of $50.

[Carpark]
1 free carpark is also included with your stay.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

table.description:
Located across the Carlton Gardens and Melbourne Museum, find yourself near fresh greenery and seasonal exhibitions waiting for you to explore. With a tram stop right at your doorstep, you have easy access to all parts of the CBD and begin exploring the shopping districts, restaurants, cafes and Melbourne's iconic laneways.

A spacious open plan living, dining and kitchen area welcomes you upon entry. The living area has been carefully fitted out to ensure that you will have an enjoyable stay. One of the sofas can be converted into a sofabed for that extra guest or two. The kitchen is also fully fitted out with all the basic cooking items, including a kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, electric oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware. A 6-seater dining table set completes the space for all your entertaining needs. To ensure you have a comfortable stay, there is a wall-mounted electric heater for you to warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.


Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.


The two bedrooms each contain a queen-sized bed, both of which come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

1 free carpark is also included with your stay.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Find yourself across the Carlton Gardens, Royal Exhibition Building, Melbourne Museum and right off Melbourne's iconic CBD filled with hundreds of shops and restaurants. This home is perfect for those who like to start their morning with a walk in the park, followed by exploring all that Melbourne city (and its suburbs) has to offer.

There is a tram stop located in front of this apartment that takes you directly into the city and to Melbourne Central Station for those who want to travel out of the city by train. Free parking is also available at this accommodation.

table.description:
Located in the heart of one of Melbourne's most prestigious suburbs, this studio apartment is open plan living at its finest. This elegant and cosy apartment is situated at Kew Junction, a short walk from Kew Shopping Centre, a myriad of renowned cafes and restaurants and various forms of public transport. Experience all that suburbian Melbourne has to offer at this gorgeous apartment.

The LIVING AREA contains a 2 seater sofabed, a 4-seater dining table, a coffee table and a flat screen TV. The space is individually furnished and extremely cosy, so you can feel right at home! There is also a heating and air-conditioning unit available, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it!

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BEDROOM AREA contains a queen bed that comes with fresh, clean luxury linens and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also a bedside table to place your belongings.

Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOM stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron for your use. The bathroom has a bathtub and a shower so you can unwind after a long day. For guests who require to do laundry, there is a separate communal coin laundry area in the building with a washing machine and dryer provided. Kindly note that this cost is not included in the overall booking.

The KITCHENETTE is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, convection stovetop, oven, cutlery and dining ware.

Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm.

-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

This comfy studio apartment is located in the heart of the inner-city suburb of Kew. You'll find yourself surrounded by various parks and reserves. Also at your doorstep is Kew Shopping Centre, supermarkets and some of Melbourne's renowned cafes and restaurants.

Getting around is easy from this conveniently located apartment. You'll have access to the 48 and 109 trams that run from Box Hill to Port Melbourne and Victoria Harbour Docklands to North Balwyn.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.

- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

table.description:
Our bright and airy two-bedroom home is tucked away in the cosy and quiet suburb of North Melbourne with a straight tram ride into the heart of Melbourne's iconic CBD. The house is charmingly furnished, decorated and equipped to make you feel right at home no matter how long or short your trip is. Find yourself located near the Melbourne Zoo, Royal Melbourne Hospital, Royal Park and a 2-minute walk away from the tram stop on Flemington Road for you to explore all that Melbourne has to offer.

[Welcome]
The living room contains beautiful timber floorboards and tasteful decorations to make you feel right at home. You will find two comfortable sofas (one of which converts into a single sofa bed for that extra guest) and a 6-seater dining table for you to entertain during your stay. To complete your stay, we have equipped the kitchen with essential cooking items, including necessary crockery, cutlery, kettle, microwave, toaster and dining ware. We also have a courtyard located in the centre of the house with a pond where you can watch our fishes swim around, as well as a quiet patio around the back of the house for you to relax and breathe in the fresh air. The home has split-system airconditioning units for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Bedrooms]
The master bedroom has a queen-sized bed, while the second bedroom contains a double-sized bed. All beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The main bathroom is located upstairs and will be prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. Downstairs you will find an additional toilet (no shower). You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron and washing machine during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
You will be able to park 1 car in the garage.

table.space:
[Welcome]
The living room contains beautiful timber floorboards and tasteful decorations to make you feel right at home. You will find two comfortable sofas (one of which converts into a single sofa bed for that extra guest) and a 6-seater dining table for you to entertain during your stay. To complete your stay, we have equipped the kitchen with essential cooking items, including necessary crockery, cutlery, kettle, microwave, toaster and dining ware. We also have a courtyard located in the centre of the house with a pond where you can watch our fishes swim around, as well as a quiet patio around the back of the house for you to relax and breathe in the fresh air. The home has split-system airconditioning units for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Bedrooms]
The master bedroom has a queen-sized bed, while the second bedroom contains a double-sized bed. All beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

[Bathrooms]
The main bathroom is located upstairs and will be prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. Downstairs you will find an additional toilet (no shower). You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron and washing machine during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
You will be able to park 1 car in the garage.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you i
table.summary: Our bright and airy two-bedroom home is tucked away in the cosy and quiet suburb of North Melbourne with a straight tram ride into the heart of Melbourne's iconic CBD. The house is charmingly furnished, decorated and equipped to make you feel right at home no matter how long or short your trip is. Find yourself located near the Melbourne Zoo, Royal Melbourne Hospital, Royal Park and a 2-minute walk away from the tram stop on Flemington Road for you to explore all that Melbourne has to offer.
table.transit: The nearest tram stop is located 5 minutes away by foot on Flemington Road. This gives you access to the city via tram number 57 or 59, and access to Flemington Bridge Train Station via tram number 59. For those with a car, there is one free secure and sheltered parking available on the premises.

table.description:
This apartment is located in "Abode", one of Melbourne's recently completed luxury residential buildings situated in the heart of Melbourne CBD. The State Library, Chinatown, Melbourne Central and Emporium shopping centres, QV, Bourke Street shopping strip and iconic Lygon Street are right at your doorstep or only a short walk away. The location, coupled with the expansive views from this 36th floor apartment, is the perfect holiday home for exploring Melbourne CBD and beyond!

[Welcome]
This apartment is the perfect base for your Melbourne adventures. Recently completed, this 2 bedroom apartment has been stylishly furnished with comfort in mind. Featuring an open plan living and dining area, the space contains a sofabed (for that additional guest if you require it), 4-seater dining set, and a fully equipped kitchen with all the essential items you will require for your entertaining needs. Soak in the expansive views from the attached balcony whilst you enjoy your morning coffee/tea or evening wine. The living area comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Sofabed]
Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

[Bedrooms]
The two bedrooms each contain a queen-sized bed, both of which come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathroom]
The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

The location is ideal for all travellers with Swanston Street downstairs, 2-min walk to Melbourne Central Station and Queen Victoria Market, access to Elizabeth Street's Asian eateries, Melbourne's GPO and Hardware Lane are down the road, Emporium and Flinders Street are a free tram-ride away. The location is ideal for all travellers with Russell Street downstairs, 2-min walk to Melbourne Central Station (hotspot) and Chinatown (hotspot), a 5-min walk to Queen Victoria Market, access to Elizabeth Street's Asian eateries, Melbourne's GPO and Hardware Lane are down the road, Emporium and Flinders Street are a free tram-ride away. We highly recommend walking next-door to K-Box for an affordable Karaoke session with some drinks any night of the week.

Although there is a free tram service in the CBD, you can find practically everything you need on foot. Walk and explore all of Melbourne's famous laneways, alleys, side streets and hidden spots.

Trams -free tram access in all directions on Swanston St, Bourke St and La Trobe St.

Travelling beyond the CBD? Conveniently, the apartment is just a 5 minute walk to Melbourne Central Train station away.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

•Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
•Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
•Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.

Excess Rubbish
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

Lost & Found
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.space:
[Welcome]
This apartment has been recently renovated and furnished for your comfort. The open plan living and dining space contains a sofa with cushions, 4-seater dining set, a flat screen TV, coffee table and board games for you and your group. The kitchen is fully equipped with essential cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, dining ware and some basic condiments for you to use. There is also a dishwasher for you to use.

[Bedrooms]
Two bedrooms each contain a queen sized bed, with high quality mattresses and comfortable bedding. The third bedroom contains two single beds. All of the beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathrooms]
The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. There is also a bathtub for those days where you want to unwind. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
1 free carpark is also included with your stay.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

table.description:
Sitauted on the edge of the city, across from Albert Park Lake and within walking distance to the Botanical Gardens, this highly sophisticated, superbly finished apartment promises a diverse and cosmopolitan city fringe lifestyle. Coupled with famous cafes like Kettle Black and The Crux & Co. a short walk away, indulge in Melbourne's famous brunches and coffee to complete your ultimate Melbourne experience.

Wake up to the sounds of birds chirping from the tree-lined streets of South Melbourne whilst you take in the view of the city and enjoy your morning coffee/tea from the balcony of this fully furnished inner city apartment. This modern apartment has been furnished with your comfort in mind. With all that you will require, including a 2-seater sofa, fully fitted out kitchen with all basic cooking items included, and a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter, you will find your stay here with us the perfect accompaniment to your Melbourne getaway. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.


Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.


The bedroom contains a queen-sized bed and comes with clean and freshly pressed linen and an all-seasons quilt to keep you warm throughout the year.


The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.


Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

This apartment is located in the fantastic suburb of South Melbourne, you'll find yourself near a multitude of famous brunch places that showcase what makes Melbourne cafes so fantastic. You'll also be near Albert Park Lake, Albert Park Golf Course and Fawkner Park..

This apartment has access to trams on Wells St (58 Tram) transversing from Toorak to West Coburg.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Located in the heart of Melbourne's iconic CBD, this abode is perfect for the avid travellers who enjoy the hustle and bustle of the city along with the convenience of accessing and exploring the other suburbs of this beautiful city. Find yourself right across the road from Southern Cross Station where you will find a Coles supermarket and Spencer Street DFO. Luxurious, affordable, comfortable and cosy - this home away from home is your first step to enjoying all that Melbourne has to offer.

The LIVING ROOM is furnished with a sofa and ample pillows, and a flat screen TV. For extra guests, the sofa pulls open to become a sofa bed. The dining area has been furnished with a 4-seater dining table for meals. There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it! 

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The master BEDROOM contains a queen bed that comes with fresh luxury linens always cleaned before you arrive, and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOM stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware.

Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you.

Find yourself in the midst of Melbourne's eclectic and vibrant CBD, with convenient access to all that the vivacious city has to offer.  Located only a stones throw from a multitude of the city's iconic attractions, you'll find yourself spoiled for choice when exploring the bustling city.  Enjoy being just walking distance from the public transport hub,  Southern Cross Station - one of Melbourne's largest train stations, major shopping destination, DFO, and Marvel Stadium. This apartment is also located near the Yarra River, and Crown Entertainment Complex. This prime location will ensure that you have quick and easy access to a large array of parks, local restaurants and shops, as well as everyday living with a Coles Supermarket only a short walk away.

This apartment is situated in a location with extreme convenience, with multiple modes of public transport right at your doorstep. You'll be staying only a minute walk from Melbourne's largest train station - Southern Cross Station. There's plenty of access to Melbourne's wide sprawling train network throughout the whole of Melbourne, as well as access to V-Line, giving you access to various towns throughout regional Victoria. This apartment is also conveniently located within the Free Tram Network. The Free Tram Network transverses from Dockland's Waterfront to the iconic Federation Square to the culturally diverse Queen Victoria Market, and everywhere between.

table.space:
The LIVING ROOM is furnished with a sofa and ample pillows, and a flat screen TV. For extra guests, the sofa pulls open to become a sofa bed. The dining area has been furnished with a 4-seater dining table for meals. There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it! 

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The master BEDROOM contains a queen bed that comes with fresh luxury linens always cleaned before you arrive, and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOM stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware.

Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you.
table.summary: Located in the heart of Melbourne's iconic CBD, this abode is perfect for the avid travellers who enjoy the hustle and bustle of the city along with the convenience of accessing and exploring the other suburbs of this beautiful city. Find yourself right across the road from Southern Cross Station where you will find a Coles supermarket and Spencer Street DFO. Luxurious, affordable, comfortable and cosy - this home away from home is your first step to enjoying all that Melbourne has to offer.
table.transit: This apartment is situated in a location with extreme convenience, with multiple modes of public transport right at your doorstep. You'll be staying only a minute walk from Melbourne's largest train station - Southern Cross Station. There's plenty of access to Melbourne's wide sprawling train network throughout the whole of Melbourne, as well as access to V-Line, giving you access to various towns throughout regional Victoria. This apartment is also conveniently located within the Free Tram Network. The Free Tram Network transverses from Dockland's Waterfront to the iconic Federation Square to the culturally diverse Queen Victoria Market, and everywhere between.

table.description:
This recently renovated apartment, situated only a short walk from the Botanical Gardens, Shrine of Remembrance and Melbourne's art precinct, is the perfect location for your Melbourne getaway. Coupled with famous cafes like Kettle Black and The Crux & Co. around the corner, indulge in Melbourne's famous brunches and coffee to complete your ultimate Melbourne experience. The tram stop right at your doorstep takes you into the city for all your shopping needs or to St Kilda beach.

A thoughtfully furnished and fitted out open plan living, dining and kitchen area welcomes you upon entry. The living area contains two leather sofas and all that you need for a comfortable stay. The balcony has a small outdoor set for you to enjoy your morning coffees/teas or evening wines. A 6-seater dining table set completes the space for all your entertaining needs. The living area comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.


Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.


The two bedrooms each contain a queen-sized bed, both of which come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.


The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.


1 free carpark is also included with your stay.


This apartment is located close to Albert Park where the Grand Prix and Australian Tennis Open take place each year.

Tram stop right in front of the apartment which is a huge bonus and it takes you straight to Swanston St in the heart of the CBD.
It is also right opposite the Botanical Gardens and only 5-min from the National Gallery of Victoria, Flinders Street station, and Federation Square - all major tourist attractions.

Inspired by Nordic interior design throughout, the open plan living and dining room features a 6-seater dining table, flat screen TV, coffee table, cosy sofa bed (that folds backwards into a bed for one for that additional guest) and a fully equipped kitchen perfect for cooking up a delicious meal. [Sofabed]

Bedrooms]

table.description:
Prima Pearl is one of Melbourne's finest apartments located directly next to the Crown Entertainment Complex. This World-Class residential tower contains an unparalleled range of luxury amenities which you will not want to miss.

The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofa, 4 seater dining set, a flat screen Smart TV with free Netflix, coffee table and comfy cushions. There are floor to ceiling windows throughout the apartment with sky views. There is a heating and airconditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it! Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BEDROOMS come with clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. Both bedrooms contain a queen sized bed, with high quality mattresses and comfortable bedding. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes. The bedrooms each have a heating- and airconditioning unit as well.

Magnificant VIEWS throughout the apartment, including both bedrooms.

The BATHROOMs are stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. In the bathroom there is also a washing machine, detergent, an iron and an ironing board.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, diningware and some basic condiments for you to use. There is also a dishwasher.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

With easy access to trams, trains, and hundreds of shops and restaurants located at your doorstep, this apartment is perfect for travellers who value convenience, luxury and comfort - a home away from home!

An open plan living, dining and kitchen space fitted out with luxurious furnishings welcomes you. The sofa also converts into a sofabed for that extra guest or two. To round off your ultimate Melbourne experience, take in the expansive city views from the enclosed winter garden balcony whilst you enjoy your morning coffees/teas or evening wines. The kitchen is also fully fitted out with basic cooking items and includes a kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, electric oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware - all that you require for a comfortable stay. The living area comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. table.space:
An open plan living, dining and kitchen space fitted out with luxurious furnishings welcomes you. The sofa also converts into a sofabed for that extra guest or two. To round off your ultimate Melbourne experience, take in the expansive city views from the enclosed winter garden balcony whilst you enjoy your morning coffees/teas or evening wines. The kitchen is also fully fitted out with basic cooking items and includes a kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, electric oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware - all that you require for a comfortable stay. The living area comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.


Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.


The bedroom contains a queen-sized bed and comes with clean and freshly pressed linen and an all-seasons quilt to keep you warm throughout the year.


The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.
table.summary:
Located in the heart of Melbourne's city on the corner of Elizabeth and Franklin Street, find yourself feeling right at home in this beautiful and modern 1-bedroom apartment comprising of a kitchen with quality European appliances and a built in wardrobe in the bedroom.
With easy access to trams, trains, and hundreds of shops and restaurants located at your doorstep, this apartment is perfect for travellers who value convenience, luxury and comfort - a home away from home!
table.transit: The apartment is conveniently located in close proximity to Melbourne Central Station. Trams are available right outside the doorstep!

table.description:
Live the high life in Melbourne's newly crowned tallest building, Australia 108. This brand new apartment is located in the heart of Southbank - near the Yarra River, National Gallery of Victoria, Royal Botanical Gardens, Crown Casino, Southbank Promenade and minutes away from the hustle and bustle of Melbourne's CBD that is filled with hundreds of restaurants and shops. Find yourself in the comfort and convenience that this home has to offer - your first step in exploring this iconic city.

The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofabed with cushions, an extendable 3-seater dining table and a flat screen smart TV. There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it!

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BEDROOM contains a queen bed that comes with fresh, clean luxury linens and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOM stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware.

Free WIFI is available in all rooms throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you.

table.description:
Located in the lovely suburb of Wantirna South, find yourself a short drive away from the Dandenong Ranges, Mount Dandenong, the iconic Puffing Billy Railway attraction, and Westfield Knox Mall. This four-bedroom house is perfect for families and large groups that want to indulge in some nature and still have easy access to Melbourne's hustle and bustle of a city - located around 40 minutes away! Free wifi is available throughout your stay, and the garage has four parking spaces for your use.

[Welcome]
The LIVING AREA is separated into a living room, lounge room, dining room and study. While the living room contains two 3-seater sofas, a coffee table and a flat screen TV, the lounge room contains a 3-seater sofa with an indoor fireplace and the dining contains a 6-seater dining table. There is central heating and air-conditioning available for use in all areas of the house, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it!

[Bedrooms]
The master, second and third BEDROOM each contain a queen sized bed, while the fourth bedroom contains 2 single beds -all of which come with fresh, clean luxury linens and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also a baby cot in the master bedroom for families with a young child, and sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

[Bathrooms]
Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOMS stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

[Kitchen]
The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stove-top, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware - perfect for those who want to whip up a meal!

[Backyard]
There is also a private YARD located at the side of the house for those who enjoy some fresh air in the morning and/or evening!

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you. There is also 4 parking spaces in the garage of the house, and street parking too.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

table.space:
[Welcome]
The LIVING AREA is separated into a living room, lounge room, dining room and study. While the living room contains two 3-seater sofas, a coffee table and a flat screen TV, the lounge room contains a 3-seater sofa with an indoor fireplace and the dining contains a 6-seater dining table. There is central heating and air-conditioning available for use in all areas of the house, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it!

[Bedrooms]
The master, second and third BEDROOM each contain a queen sized bed, while the fourth bedroom contains 2 single beds -all of which come with fresh, clean luxury linens and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also a baby cot in the master bedroom for families with a young child, and sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

[Bathrooms]
Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOMS stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

[Kitchen]
The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stove-top, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware - perfect for those who want to whip up a meal!

[Backyard]
There is also a private YARD located at the side of the house for those who enjoy some fresh air in the morning and/or evening!

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you. There is also 4 parking spaces in the garage of the house, and street parking too.
table.summary: Located in the lovely suburb of Wantirna South, find yourself a short drive away from the Dandenong Ranges, Mount Dandenong, the iconic Puffing Billy Railway attraction, and Westfield Knox Mall. This four-bedroom house is perfect for families and large groups that want to indulge in some nature and still have easy access to Melbourne's hustle and bustle of a city - located around 40 minutes away! Free wifi is available throughout your stay, and the garage has four parking spaces for your use.

table.description:
Situated on the corner of Melbourne’s iconic St Kilda Road, PARQUE is a landmark new prestige luxury apartment. With its private garden and stunning near and distant views, Parque takes luxury living to all new heights.

The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofa, a flat screen TV, coffee table and comfy cushions. We have a quiet balcony with amazing views There is a heating and airconditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it!

The BEDROOM comes with a queen bed, clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

The BATHROOM is stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. In the bathroom there is also a washing machine and dryer, detergent, an iron and an ironing board.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, induction stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, diningware and some basic condiments for you to use.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

Guest will have access to the entire apartment on Level 2 and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Groceries: Prahran Market is a 5 minute drive away.

Our luxury apartment positions you perfectly to embrace and enjoy Melbourne living to its fullest. The city's premier shopping, dining, entertainment, recreation and education precincts are only minutes away, while many of its finest coffee shops, eateries and boutiques, markets, parks and sports facilities are practically on your doorstep. 

We are a few minutes from Albert Park lake.

The tram stop is right at outside our doorstep. We are just minutes away from the city and other iconic locations like South Yarra, St Kilda Beach, Albert Park and the Prahran Market. There are also plenty of taxis and ubers around the area, with a waiting area outside the lobby for easy access.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.access:
Guest will have access to the entire home.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).
table.description:
This is the most affordable, luxurious, and spacious apartment in the Heart of Melbourne without having to sacrifice privacy.

With a Walk Score of 100/100, my home is surrounded by Melbourne's Top Restaurants, Cafes, Bars, Shopping and Entertainment. Whether it be Melbourne's secret hidden laneways, late night hotspots, day-time activities, or education institutions, my place is at the Heart of it all!

Oh, and Melbourne's best Karaoke at K-Box is next door!

The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofa, a 4-seater dining set, a big screen TV, coffee table and comfy cushions. We have amazing city views. There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it!

The BEDROOMS come with clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The main bedroom contains a queen sized bed, and the second bedroom a double bed. Both bedrooms come with high quality mattresses and comfortable bedding. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

The BATHROOMS are stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. In the bathroom there is also a washing machine and dryer, detergent, an iron and an ironing board.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, dining ware and some basic condiments for you to use.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

Guest will have access to the entire home.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

The location is ideal for all travellers with Russell Street downstairs, 2-min walk to Melbourne Central Station (hotspot) and Chinatown (hotspot), a 5-min walk to Queen Victoria Market, access to Elizabeth Street's Asian eateries, Melbourne's GPO and Hardware Lane are down the road, Emporium and Flinders Street are a free tram-ride away.

We highly recommend walking next-door to K-Box for an affordable Karaoke session with some drinks any night of the week!

I would definitely walk everywhere! How else would you get to see all of Melbourne's laneways, alleys, side streets and hidden spots? But if you want, there is free tram access in all directions on La Trobe Street and down on Swanston Street, as well as Melbourne Central's Train Station just a 5-7 minute walk away!

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Perfectly situated near Melbourne Airport and Melbourne CBD, this Scandinavian-inspired luxury townhouse is suited for travellers intending to travel around Melbourne that may not want to stay directly in the CBD. With cliffside views next to a tranquil lake, our place is a relaxing getaway only 10-15 Mins to the Airport, and 15-20 Mins from the CBD. 3 fully-furnished bedrooms, spacious living & dining room, fully-equipped kitchen, balcony, 2 bathrooms with rain showers, and WiFi + Netflix.

[Welcome]
Enjoy this modern and spacious fully furnished 3 bedroom home. The living space is fitted out with all that you will need for a comfortable stay. The kitchen is fully equipped with all the essential kitchen utensils, kettle, toaster and dining wares to get you started on your stay. Take in the peaceful surrounds and view of the lake from the attached balcony. The living area and master bedrooms come with split-system air-conditioning units for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Bedrooms]
The Master Bedroom has a queen bed, large walk in robe, and ensuite. Bedrooms #2 and #3 each have a double bed, a full length mirrored wardrobe, and bedside tables with lamps. All beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathrooms]
The bathrooms are prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
You will be able to park 1 car in the garage. Should you have more than 1 car, you may park a 2nd car in the driveway outside the garage. Please do not block the pedestrian walkway with your cars.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

[Netflix]
Password to the Netflix account will be included in the guest manual.

With cliffside views next to a tranquil lake, our place is a relaxing getaway only 10-15 Mins to the Airport, and 15-20 Mins from the CBD. 3 fully-furnished bedrooms, spacious living & dining room, fully-equipped kitchen, balcony, 2 bathrooms with rain showers, and WiFi + Netflix.
table.transit: Our home is around 10-15 min walk to the nearest bus stop. It is most suited as a family holiday home, who own or have rented a car.

[Check-in]

-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.

[Check-out]

table.description:
Live the high life in Melbourne's newly crowned tallest building, Australia 108. This brand new apartment is located in the heart of Southbank - near the Yarra River, National Gallery of Victoria, Royal Botanical Gardens, Crown Casino, Southbank Promenade and minutes away from the hustle and bustle of Melbourne's CBD that is filled with endless cafes, restaurants and shops. Find yourself in the comfort and convenience that this home has to offer - your first step in exploring this iconic city!

[Welcome]
Welcome to the tallest residential building in Melbourne! The expansive views of the city, luxurious renovations and cosy furnishings invite you into this apartment. Featuring an open plan living and dining space, the apartment is fully furnished with a sofabed for that extra guest, 4-seater bar style dining table, enclosed winter garden balcony, and a kitchen kitted out with all the cookings essentials you will require for your entertaining purposes. The living area also comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Sofabed]
Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

[Bedrooms]
The bedrooms each contains a queen-sized bed and comes with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathroom & Laundry]
The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. WIFI details will be provided to you in the guest manual prior to your check-in.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Find yourself minutes away from Southbank Promenade, Royal Botanical Gardens, the National Gallery of Victoria, Crown Casino and the Melbourne's iconic CBD that is filled with hundreds of restaurants, cafes, bars and shopping options for you to enjoy!

Trams are available on Queensbridge Street, with the nearest train station being Flinders Street Railway Station.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.
