table.description:
Located only 30 minutes away from Melbourne's CBD, this home is the embodiment of a perfect getaway. Situated in the lovely suburb of Hawthorn within walking distance from Glenferrie Road shops and restaurants, this large four bedroom house is the perfect retreat for families or large groups. Immerse yourself in resort style serenity while you lounge in the enclosed outdoor pool, or treat yourself to a game of billiards or basketball. Free wifi is accessible throughout your stay.

[Welcome]
Our obsession with Bali was the inspiration for this home. Built with organic materials and textures, warmth and comfort was the focus with our furnishings. This home is the ultimate family getaway with several break out areas for entertaining and relaxing, and includes a billiards table and pool. There is also a spacious and fully equipped kitchen with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware - perfect for those who want to whip up a meal! A 6-seater dining table set completes the space for all your entertaining needs. There is central heating and air-conditioning available for use in all areas of the house for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.


The alfresco area and private pool is the highlight of the property and is located at the side of the house. Indulge in a swim in warmer weather or enjoy your morning coffees and evening wines whilst you soak in the tropical surrounds in the tropical backyard.

[Bedrooms]
All four bedrooms each contain a queen-sized bed, all of which come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The master bedroom has a generous walk-in-wardrobe and private bathroom with tub to complete your spa experience.

[Bathrooms]
The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
You will be able to park 2 cars along the driveway outside the garage. Please do not block the pedestrian walkway with your cars.

[Wifi]
Free WIFI is availabl

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Find yourself in the cosy suburb of Hawthorn - right in front of Fairview Park which is along the Yarra River. You can spend the day visiting the Melbourne Tram Museum, or visit the Boroondara Farmers Market (open on Saturdays) and Camberwell Sunday Market. Additionally, located on Glenferrie Road and Burnley Road are restaurants and shops for those who want to shop and dine!

There are trams available on Riversdale Road, a 5 minute walk away from the accommodation, or take a train from Hawthorn Station (accessible by tram no. 75). For those with a car, access the hustle and bustle of Melbourne's CBD which is located just 30 minutes away.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Located right in the middle of this iconic city, this apartment is perfect for those who enjoy having hundreds of shops, restaurants and Melbourne's little laneways at your doorstep for you to explore. Find yourself a 5 minute walk away from Melbourne Central and Flagstaff Station - the perfect place for those who appreciate convenience and a modern, urban abode!

The LIVING ROOM contains a 2 seater sofabed, a 4-seater dining table, a coffee table and a flat screen TV. There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it! 

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The master BEDROOM contains a queen bed that comes with fresh, clean luxury linens and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOM stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stovetop, oven, cutlery and dining ware.

Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Our apartment is conveniently located right in the heart of the city, only a stone's throw away from central shopping strips and shopping malls such as Melbourne Central and Emporium, surrounded by an array of top restaurants, cafes and bars. Attractions just a stone's throw away include the historical Hellenic Musuem and Royal Mint, the lush Flagstaff Gardens, the famous Queen Victoria Market and the iconic Magistrates Courts of Melbourne.

Melbourne city is serviced by an amazing network of free trams for travel within the city's free tram zone. Trams and trains will also take you further out into the suburbs. Navigating around the city is easy; simply open up (Hidden by Airbnb) Maps, and select the public transport option for easy guidance to tram/train stops, and what number tram/train to take.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

The Istana, an ideal luxury lifestyle within the heart of Melbourne CBD. With amazing amenities and within walking distance to Melbourne Central Station and Flatstaff Station, our stylish and modern apartment is perfect for your stay.

The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofa with comfy cushions, a 6 seater dining set, a flat screen Smart TV (With free Netflix). We have a quiet balcony with city views. There is a heating and airconditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it! Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. The request for sofabed will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. The BEDROOMS come with clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. Both bedrooms contain queen sized beds, high quality mattresses and comfortable bedding. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

The BATHROOM is stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. In the bathroom there is also a washing machine and dryer, detergent, an iron and an ironing board.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, diningware and some basic condiments for you to use. There is also a dishwasher.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

Shopaholics can walk to premier shopping destinations Melbourne Central, Emporium, QV, Bourke Street Mall and flagship Myer and H&M stores.

Food lovers can walk to the gastronomic delights of Queen Victoria Market, Hardware Lane’s intimate restaurants, Chinatown, Lygon Street and over 1,000 restaurants and bars in the CBD and riverside in Southbank.

Although the free tram service is all around my place, I can walk in any direction and find everything I need. I have lived here my whole life, so please do ask me for any tips on the best eating places. There are new things springing up every year and certain activities are seasonal so I would be more than happy to help you plan your stay. I have eaten almost everywhere, however, even I find some new secret places every now and then.
Walk and see all of Melbourne's famous laneways, alleys, side streets and hidden spots.

Trams
-Free tram access in all directions on Swanston Street and Elizabeth Street.
-There are also some trams directly to popular inner suburban hotspots (Richmond, South Yarra, Brunswick, South Melbourne).

Train
-5 min walk to Melbourne Central Station or Flagstaff Station for all train lines to visit nearby suburbs.

Also close by is the Melbourne Visitor Shuttle, Free City Circle Tram, Melbourne Bike Share and the Sky Bus Hotel Transfer will even drop you off at Pegasus Apart'Hotel.

table.space:
The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofa with comfy cushions, a 6 seater dining set, a flat screen Smart TV (With free Netflix). We have a quiet balcony with city views. There is a heating and airconditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it! Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. The request for sofabed will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BEDROOMS come with clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. Both bedrooms contain queen sized beds, high quality mattresses and comfortable bedding. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

The BATHROOM is stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. In the bathroom there is also a washing machine and dryer, detergent, an iron and an ironing board.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, diningware and some basic condiments for you to use. There is also a dishwasher.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.
table.street: 1016/228 A'Beckett St, West Melbourne, VIC 3003, Australia
table.summary: The Istana, an ideal luxury lifestyle within the heart of Melbourne CBD. With amazing amenities and within walking distance to Melbourne Central Station and Flatstaff Station, our stylish and modern apartment is perfect for your stay.
table.transit:
Although the free tram service is all around my place, I can walk in any direction and find everything I need. I have lived here my whole life, so please do ask me for any tips on the best eating places. There are new things springing up every year and certain activities are seasonal so I would be more than happy to help you plan your stay. I have eaten almost everywhere, however, even I find some new secret places every now and then.
Walk and see all of Melbourne's famous laneways, alleys, side streets and hidden spots.

Trams
-Free tram access in all directions on Swanston Street and Elizabeth Street.
-There are also some trams directly to popular inner suburban hotspots (Richmond, South Yarra, Brunswick, South Melbourne).

Train
-5 min walk to Melbourne Central Station or Flagstaff Station for all train lines to visit nearby suburbs.

Also close by is the Melbourne Visitor Shuttle, Free City Circle Tram, Melbourne Bike Share and the Sky Bus Hotel Transfer will even drop you off at Pegasus Apart'Hotel.

hosts.about:
Roomerang is an end-to-end short stays team based in Melbourne.

We are avid travellers and know how hard it can be to find comfortable and cosy, yet affordable accommodation. We try to remove all the complications surrounding your stay, so you can focus on other important aspects of your trip. And if you feel we have left anything out, let us know and we would love to help.

Roomerang provides professionally cleaned and well-kept, affordable stays presenting you with a home to return to no matter who you are, where you're from or what you are here for!

table.description:
This spacious apartment is situated in the grand five-storey heritage building that is Fairfax House. This CBD abode is located in the very heart of Melbourne City and you'll find all of the best gems that Melbourne CBD has to offer at your doorstep. Stay in this comfortable apartment and find yourself surrounded by eclectic bars and restaurants, iconic landmarks such as Block Arcade and a myriad of shopping destinations including the must see Bourke Street Mall.

The LIVING ROOM contains two comfortable sofas, a 6-seater dining set, a flat screen TV and coffee table. There is a window to light up the room. There is heating and an air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it!

The BEDROOMS are accessible via a set of stairs from the living area, with beds that come with clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

The BATHROOMS are stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. There is a bathtub available in one of the bathrooms.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located in the heart of Melbourne's bustling CBD, this apartment is the epitome of convenience. Surrounded by Melbourne's iconic attractions, such as Block Arcade, Bourke Street Mall, St Paul's Cathedral and Melbourne's famous restaurants, bars and cafes, you'll find yourself spoilt for choice!

This city apartment is located near a multitude of public transport. Located in the Free Tram Zone, you can easily catch a tram on Elizabeth Street or take a train from Flinders St Railway Station. Getting around will be a breeze.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Prima Pearl is one of Melbourne's most prestigious apartments located directly next to the Crown Entertainment Complex. This World-Class residential tower contains an unparalleled range of luxury amenities which you will not want to miss. Our apartment is ideal for watching the fireworks during the festive seasons!

The LIVING ROOM contains a 3 seater leather sofa, a rotating round leather sofa, a comfortable sofa bed, 6 seater dining set, a study desk, a big flat screen TV. There is a heating and airconditioning unit in the lliving room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it! The remote controlled blackout roller blinds will also prevent sunlight from entering the living room if required. Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BEDROOMS come with luxury linens and quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The master bedroom has an ensuite bathroom and a king sized bed. The second bedroom has two single beds and the third bedroom has a queen sized bed. ALL bedrooms come with high quality mattresses, comfortable bedding and sufficient storage space for your beloingings and clothes. All bedrooms have magnificant views and remote controlled roller blinds for you to sleep in. Each room has its own airconditioning and heating unit as well.

The BATHROOMS are stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. Our bathrooms also have heated towel racks if you prefer warm towels after your shower. Our master bedroom also comes with a make up mirror for the ladies.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, microwave, oven, toaster, cutlery, diningware and basic condiments for you to use. We have a boiling and sparkling water dispenser attached to the kitchen sink, refer to manual on how to operate. We also provide a dishwasher.

LAUNDRY ROOM has a washing machine and dryer, a vacuum cleaner, an iron and an ironing board.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Directly next to Crown Casino and Freshwater Place. Minutes walk to Flinders Station. World renowned Restaurants such as NOBU, Rockpool Bar and Grill, and Meat Wine and Co are a minute walk away. Bustling bars and restaurants all along the river. Grocery stores and convenience stores around the corner on City Road. Golden Village Cinema in Crown Complex. Designer stores such as Prada, Luis Vuitton, Rolex and many more in the Crown Complex! Right next to Yarra River and CBD.

Potential for noise: You may hear a whistling noise coming from the building during periods of high winds. Please note that this is normal and nothing to worry about.

Taxi ranks in Crown Casino / Crown Promenade.
Tram stop on Queensbridge street into CBD right at your doorstep.
Just a short walk across the yarra river to Flinders Train Station and the CBD.

- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.

- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.space:
The LIVING ROOM contains a 3 seater leather sofa, a rotating round leather sofa, a comfortable sofa bed, 6 seater dining set, a study desk, a big flat screen TV. There is a heating and airconditioning unit in the lliving room, but please switch it off when not in use, we deeply appreciate it! The remote controlled blackout roller blinds will also prevent sunlight from entering the living room if required. Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BEDROOMS come with luxury linens and quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The master bedroom has an ensuite bathroom and a king sized bed. The second bedroom has two single beds and the third bedroom has a queen sized bed. ALL bedrooms come with high quality mattresses, comfortable bedding and sufficient storage space for your beloingings and clothes. All bedrooms have magnificant views and remote controlled roller blinds for you to sleep in. Each room has its own airconditioning and heating unit as well.

The BATHROOMS are stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. Our bathrooms also have heated towel racks if you prefer warm towels after your shower. Our master bedroom also comes with a make up mirror for the ladies.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, microwave, oven, toaster, cutlery, diningware and basic condiments for you to use. We have a boiling and sparkling water dispenser attached to the kitchen sink, refer to manual on how to operate. We also provide a dishwasher.

LAUNDRY ROOM has a washing machine and dryer, a vacuum cleaner, an iron and an ironing board.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

table.description:
Our tastefully furnished and fully-equipped one bedroom one bathroom apartment provides everything you need to experience a brilliant, memorable holiday. Featuring a bright living & dining area with wraparound balcony, enjoy the beautiful sun, sand, and sea surrounds of the beautiful Gold Coast from your very own seaside sanctuary. Situated just one street from the ocean, one street from the Light Rail network & within a short stroll of two shopping centres, you'll always be at heart of it all.

Newly installed hardwood floors welcome you into this thoughtfully furnished apartment in the heart of Surfers Paradise. Enjoy a morning coffee/tea or evening wine on the wraparound balcony whilst you take in the view; or whip up a home cooked meal in the recently renovated kitchen. The living area comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.


The bedroom contains a queen-sized bed, and a bunk bed which sleeps an additional two guests. All beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.


The bathroom is prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and drying rack during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.

- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]

table.name: Wizarding Room of Melbourne

user.about:
Greetings fellow Jedi!

My name is Marini...

Star Wars and Harry Potter nerd, a property developer, part-time property sales executive, and a passionate latin dancer!

Food & dessert lover, who loves going to Victorian country side to harvest my own honey.. 

Most of my travels have been done either solo or with my best travel buddy (my super-cool-a-little-shopaholic Mama!). I love going to historic places, learning different cultures, visiting museums and admiring the architecture of different countries. 

My favourite travel destinations so far are Japan and New York... and Europe!!! 
I recently just visited Europe with my Mama. We went to Milan, Lake Como, Turino, Geneva, Montreux, and Paris... my my my I knew Europe was pretty...but I was NOT expecting to fall head over heel with her!  And the soaps they have there.... heavenly!

Our next trip is to visit Prague and Stockholm... I'm beyooonnddddd excitedddd!!!!

My style of travelling is definitely NOT to pack light. We have a big family and we can't leave anyone behind when it comes to gifts! I remember coming back from New York with my Mama with 12 suitcases.. all filled with gifts for our friends and family...LOL! Below is a very common conversation between myself and either the hotel concierge, or the taxi driver:

Concierge/Driver: "Are you travelling with your family, Miss?"
Me: "Yes I am actually...*sheepishly* a family of 2"  
Concierge/Driver: "WHHHATTTTTTT"

HAHAHHHAH!! Yup! Every. Single. Time.

Anyways, my passion in life is to build relationships with the people around me. I love reading other people's success stories, and it makes me sooo happy when I see the people around me succeed in life. I strongly believe that when you share more in life, and the more you help others, the more generous life will be towards you... and I feel this in my life daily.

Soooo.... lately I have been a little bit curious with DIY home projects... making truffle honey, homemade artisan soaps, and natural beauty products... So you might just get lucky and randomly get some home-made stuff from me when you book my place! LOL!

I recently just visited Europe with my Mama. We went to Milan, Lake Como, Turino, Geneva, Montreux, and Paris... my my my I knew Europe was pretty...but I was NOT expecting to fall head over heel with her!  And the soaps they have there.... heavenly!

Our next trip is to visit Prague and Stockholm... I'm beyooonnddddd excitedddd!!!!

My style of travelling is definitely NOT to pack light. We have a big family and we can't leave anyone behind when it comes to gifts! I remember coming back from New York with my Mama with 12 suitcases.. all filled with gifts for our friends and family...LOL! Below is a very common conversation between myself and either the hotel concierge, or the taxi driver:

Concierge/Driver: "Are you travelling with your family, Miss?"
Me: "Yes I am actually...*sheepishly* a family of 2"  
Concierge/Driver: "WHHHATTTTTTT"

HAHAHHHAH!! Yup! Every. Single. Time.

Anyways, my passion in life is to build relationships with the people around me. I love reading other people's success stories, and it makes me sooo happy when I see the people around me succeed in life. I strongly believe that when you share more in life, and the more you help others, the more generous life will be towards you... and I feel this in my life daily.

Soooo.... lately I have been a little bit curious with DIY home projects... making truffle honey, homemade artisan soaps, and natural beauty products... So you might just get lucky and randomly get some home-made stuff from me when you book my place! LOL!

A true fan’s home, secretly located north of the big city of Melbourne, all visitors must swear an unbreakable vow to keep the location from being discovered by Muggles!

In this room, you may choose to sleep aboard the Train Cabin or in the Magical School Dorm, take mugshots like a Wanted Prisoner, and try on a Broomstick! 
BYO Buttahbeer, and access the Department of Magic!

Have Fun!

Welcome to the Wizarding Room of Melbourne...featuring original, vintage and new memorabilia inspired by our most favourite magical childhood novels. This brand new, spacious and modern apartment is conveniently located in North Melbourne, approximately 5 minutes from Melbourne CBD. 

DISCLAIMER:
Please note that The Wizarding Room of Melbourne is not endorsed by and have no association or affiliation with the Harry Potter & the Cursed Child play, the Harry Potter novels, movies and related intellectual property or their respective rights holders. All items in the Wizarding Room of Melbourne are personal collection and home decor of the Host. 

FREE PARKING on the premise is available throughout your stay (1 car).


LIVING ROOM

- Spacious and modern with pull out 3-seater sofa bed that sleeps 2 people.

- Super fast unlimited NBN Wi-Fi for minimal to no buffering time during Netflix!

- 55” Smart HDTV with Netflix enabled, so you can stream all the latest movies and re-watch all the Harry Potter sequels.

- North facing window allowing ample of natural light into the apartment

- Block out blinds so you can sleep in til late even on the sofa bed.

- Spacious working space for business travellers.

- Quiet & Cozy fun balcony

- Board Games for family fun time

- AND many many more amazing magical items that will bring back so much happy memory from your childhood..



KITCHEN
-A pantry fully stocked with a range of tea & coffee to help you start your day. 

-French Press Coffee/Tea maker, Toaster & Electric Kettles

-Fully equipped kitchen, including pots & pans, tumblers, mugs, and dining set.




BEDROOMS
- Posture-pedic queen size mattress with 2 different themes

- Block out blinds to prevent sun glare from waking you up too early

- Massive wardrobe to fit all your clothes and costumes!


BATHROOMS
- Rainmaker head shower & detachable hand-held shower, with complimentary body wash, shampoo, conditioner, and liquid hand soap.

- Nice fluffy towels and hair dryer to help you care for your witch’s mane..



LAUNDRY
- Washing Machine & Dryer so you'll never run out of clean robes

- laundry liquid/powder, or BYO preferred.

- Iron & Ironing board, don't step out in a creased robe!

The whole Wizarding Room / Apartment is yours to enjoy on your own with complete privacy. We offer a simple check-in process so that you can arrive any time after the official check-in time of 3PM. 

The apartment building has a common shared rooftop herb garden which guests can access.

Please do inform us of the number of guests upon booking, and if you will require extra blankets.

BEFORE ARRIVAL:
We will send you all the information that you will need to ensure a smooth arrival and check-in process. 
- Our Key Ninja Team will contact you prior to your arrival to organise a key delivery. 

Please do not hesitate to ask us any question you have. 

AFTER ARRIVAL:
 We will usually message our guests after arrival to check if they needed anything, and we are always more than happy to provide recommendations. 

MEETING WITH HOST:
As I am working full time and travelling for work a lot, I do not usually meet my guests. 
But when I am in Melbourne, we might bump into each other in the lift... If you recognise me, please say hi!! I won't cast a spell on you.

ISSUES:
If a problem arise, please contact me via AirBnB. My co-host and I are very fast in responding, and we will always try to resolve any issue as soon as possible.

Get the perfect mix of quiet residential life and the convenience of city life when you stay here. North Melbourne has breakfast cafes and boutique shops to enjoy close by, or drive just five minutes to the heart of the Central Business District.

- The apartment is 20mins taxi/uber ride from the Melbourne Airport. 

- Or you can take the Skybus to Southern Cross Station, and catch an uber to the apartment (Uber will cost around $6)

- Nearest tram stop is only 1 block away. Catch tram no. 57 from Errol St or Victoria St to go to the city. 

- Or you can enjoy a short 5-10 minute walk to Elizabeth St.

- Queen Victoria Market is only 5-10 minutes away by foot, where you can find lots of fun shopping and eateries...

- Visit the nearby Lygon St for an authentic Italian dining experience...

- FREE PARKING is available throughout your stay for 1 car. Affordable street-parking available in front of the apartment building.

DISCOUNTS:
Please note we do not offer additional discounts above those already provided for weekly stays. 
Our Wizarding Room is competitively priced, and we take pride into offering an excellent, fun and unique experience to all our guests. We are not merely offering a clean place to sleep.


A FEW RULES:

- MEDIA: While all guests are allowed to take photos and videos to post on social media regarding your stay in the apartment, we do not allow - Any commercial event / interview with any entity or party to take place in the premise. - No commercial video making is to take place without the approval or explicit consent from us.

- NO SHOES in the apartment/bedroom. Please take your shoes off at the entrance, and place them on the tiled area near the entrance. 

- All props in the glass cabinet are meant to be locked in. Please do not try to access them. 

- DO NOT MOVE or SWING on Dementor-looking creature. Or it will give you a kiss..

- Do NOT touch the LEGOs and puzzles

- Whilst I encourage you to have fun with the board games, wands and brooms provided, please be mindful of the neighbours and keep the noise to a minimum level after hours. 

- Do not take any prop out of the apartment. 

- Whilst the apartment is children friendly, please do ask your children to be gentle with the toys. 

- Please immediately inform us if any damage occurred. Excessive cleaning and/or any damage to items in the apartment will result in payment request to guests. 

- STRICTLY NO PARTIES!

All my memorabilia are very precious to me and sourced either during my holidays in the USA, and are part of my personal collection. Please do treat them with care like you would your own. Any breakage will result in bond deduction or more.
table.directions:
Meet-up Key Delivery

Our Key Ninja will call you prior to arrival to organise a suitable time for key delivery.

Upon check out they will also call you to organise a key pick up.

Your apartment is located in the back building. When you enter the apartment from the street, go pass the first corridor, out the first building and across the courtyard. You will need to swipe your key again to enter the second building. 

CARPARK ACCESS
The apartment comes with a FREE secure carpark within the premise. 
Carpark entrance is located to the left of the building (when you're standing facing the building). 
Once you have obtained your keys, drive your car to the carpark entrance, and use the black carpark remote to open the gate (press button 1). The gate will automatically close behind you. 
Park in the space marked as "B1-23”

There are also ample of on-street parking space in the area. 

The closest tram stop is on Errol St, with tram 57 taking you to the CBD via Victoria St, Elizabeth St, and Queen Victoria Market.

Roomerang is an end-to-end short stays team based in Melbourne.

We are avid travellers and know how hard it can be to find comfortable and cosy, yet affordable accommodation. We try to remove all the complications surrounding your stay, so you can focus on other important aspects of your trip. And if you feel we have left anything out, let us know and we would love to help.

Roomerang provides professionally cleaned and well-kept, affordable stays presenting you with a home to return to no matter who you are, where you're from or what you are here for!

table.description:
Situated in a prime location on a quiet street, and the BEST location to be at for the AFL Grand Final and Australian Open, this centrally located apartment home is only a short stroll from the trendy restaurants/cafes/bars/shops on Swan St and Bridge Rd Richmond. Walking distance to the public transport, and the City Centre, Chapel St, MCG, Tennis Centre, Hisense Arena, Olympic Park Sports Precinct and the Yarra River, this apartment offers you a premier location for any visit to Melbourne.

[Welcome]
This one bedroom apartment is decorated in a modern and contemporary style. It has a spacious living and dining area with a newly renovated, fully equipped kitchen with all the expected modern appliances. 

[Bedrooms]
The bedroom has a queen bed and built in robes. All linen, towels and basic essentials are provided.

[Bathrooms]
The bathroom has also been newly renovated and there is a laundry area with washing machine and dryer.

[Cooling/Heating]
There is air conditioning and heater in the apartment.

[Carpark]
There is one off street car space that comes with the apartment. There is also street parking which has daily parking restrictions.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

This secure and well maintained apartment is in a premier position. Walk to Bridge Rd & Swan Street's cafes & shopping strips, Melbourne's sporting precinct (Olympic park), and transport - with trams and Richmond Railway Station only a short distance away.

Trams are only 5 mins away either to Bridge Road or Swan street, a great position to get to all major sporting events / Melbourne City / Rod Laver Arena/ MCG.
The best and easiest way to access the property from the Airport is via Uber. Usually this takes 45min depending on traffic and costs approx. $50 AUD total. Alternatively you can take a shuttle bus to Southern Cross Station ($18/person) and then the train from Southern Cross Station to Richmond Station ($4 / person) 1.25hr trip. It's a 7 minute walk to the apartment from Richmond Station. Google maps has full transport route and time details for travel in Melbourne.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.space:
[Welcome]
This one bedroom apartment is decorated in a modern and contemporary style. It has a spacious living and dining area with a newly renovated, fully equipped kitchen with all the expected modern appliances. 

[Bedrooms]
The bedroom has a queen bed and built in robes. All linen, towels and basic essentials are provided.

[Bathrooms]
The bathroom has also been newly renovated and there is a laundry area with washing machine and dryer.

[Cooling/Heating]
There is air conditioning and heater in the apartment.

[Carpark]
There is one off street car space that comes with the apartment. There is also street parking which has daily parking restrictions.
table.summary: Situated in a prime location on a quiet street, and the BEST location to be at for the AFL Grand Final and Australian Open, this centrally located apartment home is only a short stroll from the trendy restaurants/cafes/bars/shops on Swan St and Bridge Rd Richmond. Walking distance to the public transport, and the City Centre, Chapel St, MCG, Tennis Centre, Hisense Arena, Olympic Park Sports Precinct and the Yarra River, this apartment offers you a premier location for any visit to Melbourne.
table.transit:
Trams are only 5 mins away either to Bridge Road or Swan street, a great position to get to all major sporting events / Melbourne City / Rod Laver Arena/ MCG.
The best and easiest way to access the property from the Airport is via Uber. Usually this takes 45min depending on traffic and costs approx. $50 AUD total. Alternatively you can take a shuttle bus to Southern Cross Station ($18/person) and then the train from Southern Cross Station to Richmond Station ($4 / person) 1.25hr trip. It's a 7 minute walk to the apartment from Richmond Station. Google maps has full transport route and time details for travel in Melbourne.

table.access:
Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).
table.description:
Albert Park, National Gallery of Victoria, Crown Casino and the CBD are just minutes away from our beautifully furnished, stunning apartment. This listing is the perfect retreat!

The LIVING ROOM contains a comfortable sofa bed with cushions, 2-seater dining set, a flat-screen TV and a coffee table. We have a quiet balcony with amazing views There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use, we highly appreciate it.

The BEDROOM comes with clean luxury linen and all seasons quilt to keep you warm throughout the year, equipped with a queen-sized bed, high-quality mattresses and hotel-quality pillows. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes. There is an iron and ironing board in the cupboards. 

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

The BATHROOM is stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper, bath towels and a hair dryer.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, dining ware and some basic condiments for you to use. There is also a dishwasher with dishwashing tablets and liquid.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Find yourself minutes away from Albert Park, the National Gallery of Victoria, Crown Casino and the Melbourne's iconic CBD that is filled with hundreds of restaurants, cafes, bars and shopping options for you to enjoy!

Trams are available on St Kilda Rd, with the nearest train station being Flinders Street Railway Station.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Situated directly across from Crown Casino and a short commute to the CBD via tram, our apartment is the perfect location for your Melbourne getaway. The views from the balcony, coupled with all that Crown has to offer, indulge in the best of Melbourne's entertainment, dining and shopping to complete your ultimate Melbourne experience. The tram stop right at your doorstep conveniently takes you into the city and beyond.

[Welcome]
A thoughtfully furnished and fitted out open plan living, dining and kitchen area welcomes you upon entry. The spacious living area contains a three-seater couch, armchair and all that you need for a comfortable stay. The balcony has a small outdoor set for you to enjoy your morning coffees/teas or evening wines. The kitchen is equipped all the essentials you will require for your convenience and comfort. A 6-seater dining table set completes the space for all your entertaining needs. The living area comes with a split-system airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use.

[Bedrooms]
The three bedrooms each contain a queen-sized bed, all of which come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year.

[Bathrooms]
There are two bathrooms equipped with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. The main bathroom has a bathtub - perfect for you to unwind after a long day of exploring Melbourne! Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcome to use the hairdryer, iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
1 free carpark is also included with your stay - subject to availability, so be sure to ask us!

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located directly across from Crown Casino, you will have access to 24 hours of endless fun. For entertainment, Crown houses a world-class casino, cinema, arcade, bowling alley and more. It also has a large array of top notched restaurants and bars for you to choose from. To complete your indulgence, have a browse through the selection of luxury boutiques or head up to Crown spa for a massage or facial. All of these within a few steps away from the apartment!

A tram stop is right at your door step. The no. 96 tram will take you into the heart of the CBD and beyond. Enjoy Melbourne's famous cafes, restaurants, shopping and all that our beautiful city has to offer!

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

Free onsite under-cover parking (please advise if required), free fast unlimited internet (wifi available), Netflix, 50" Full HD LCD television, full kitchen facilities, laundry washer and dryer, ironing facilities, air-conditioning/heating system and a portacot.

This apartment sleeps 4 adults quite comfortably, with a Queen sized bed in the bedroom and a sofabed which folds out to a double bed in the living room. Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request.

The apartment is completely self-contained with all linen and toweling provided. The apartment is serviced every 7 days from check-in.

NOTE: The request for sofabed will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Perfectly situated away from the hustle and bustle of the city, yet only 100 meters from the Crown Entertainment Complex which boasts over 40 restaurants, cafes and bars, cinemas, an indoor amusement park plus a live entertainment theatre and two night clubs.
Across the road is the Melbourne Exhibition Centre, and only a short walk to Southbank Promenade, South Wharf Direct Factory Outlet and Docklands.

500m is South Melbourne Market, one of Melbourne's most popular markets with over 133 businesses operating in the market and featuring a huge variety of fresh food, clothing, gifts and services.

Venture anywhere around Melbourne with the convenience of a tram stop right at your door step!

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

user.about:
Greetings fellow Jedi!

My name is Marini...

Star Wars and Harry Potter nerd, a property developer, part-time property sales executive, and a passionate latin dancer!

Food & dessert lover, who loves going to Victorian country side to harvest my own honey.. 

Most of my travels have been done either solo or with my best travel buddy (my super-cool-a-little-shopaholic Mama!). I love going to historic places, learning different cultures, visiting museums and admiring the architecture of different countries. 

My favourite travel destinations so far are Japan and New York... and Europe!!! 
I recently just visited Europe with my Mama. We went to Milan, Lake Como, Turino, Geneva, Montreux, and Paris... my my my I knew Europe was pretty...but I was NOT expecting to fall head over heel with her!  And the soaps they have there.... heavenly!

Our next trip is to visit Prague and Stockholm... I'm beyooonnddddd excitedddd!!!!

My style of travelling is definitely NOT to pack light. We have a big family and we can't leave anyone behind when it comes to gifts! I remember coming back from New York with my Mama with 12 suitcases.. all filled with gifts for our friends and family...LOL! Below is a very common conversation between myself and either the hotel concierge, or the taxi driver:

Concierge/Driver: "Are you travelling with your family, Miss?"
Me: "Yes I am actually...*sheepishly* a family of 2"  
Concierge/Driver: "WHHHATTTTTTT"

HAHAHHHAH!! Yup! Every. Single. Time.

Anyways, my passion in life is to build relationships with the people around me. I love reading other people's success stories, and it makes me sooo happy when I see the people around me succeed in life. I strongly believe that when you share more in life, and the more you help others, the more generous life will be towards you... and I feel this in my life daily.

Soooo.... lately I have been a little bit curious with DIY home projects... making truffle honey, homemade artisan soaps, and natural beauty products... So you might just get lucky and randomly get some home-made stuff from me when you book my place! LOL!

table.description:
YESS! THIS IS THE STAR WARS inspired AIRBNB YOU SEE ON THE NEWS

Reviews from our past guests:

★"Just brilliant you must experience for yourself!!"
★"Fantastic Star Wars inspired apartment, wonderfully clean and walking distance to Melbourne CBD"
★"Simply the best AirBnB I have ever stayed in!"
★"Amazing from start to finish. We will be back."
★"Very clean, the bed is super comfy & the place over all is a 10/10"
★"All my friends were jealous"
★"Such a unique apartment in a great part of town"

1 Bedroom, 1 SofaBed, 1 Bathroom, 1 Carpark

Sleeps 4

Don’t have an AirBnB account? Use this link to receive a credit off your first stay: www.airbnb.com.au/r/marinit1

Welcome to the StarWarsBnB – the first and only Star Wars inspired AirBnB in Australia, located in North Melbourne, approximately 5 minutes from Melbourne CBD. 
Stay in a true Star Wars fan's home featuring original, vintage and new memorabilia from George Lucas’ famous movie series.  

FREE PARKING on the premise is available throughout your stay (1 car).


LIVING ROOM
- Spacious and modern with pull out 3-seater sofa bed that sleeps 2 people.

- Super fast unlimited NBN Wi-Fi for minimal to no buffering time during Netflix!

- 46" Smart HDTV connected to Apple TV & Blu Ray Player, so you can stream all the latest movies and re-watch all the Star Wars sequels.

- Han Solo Bar Fridge

- Vintage Life Size R2D2 and C3P0 to welcome you as soon as you step into the apartment

- SUPER AWESOME lightsabers & voice changing masks for your Jedi-training

- Retro CANDY VENDING MACHINE will bring you back to your childhood

- SEGA Star Projector makes you feel like you are sleeping under the stars

- North facing window allowing ample of natural light into the apartment

- Block out blinds so you can sleep in til late even on the sofa bed.

- Spacious working space for business travellers.

- Quiet & Cozy balcony looking out to a central courtyard filled with lush greeneries, a perfect breakfast spot!

- Board Games for family fun time

- AND many other AMAZING Star Wars gears and toys that you can play with or admire



KITCHEN
-A pantry fully stocked with a range of breakfast items, tea & coffee to help you start your day. 

-French Press Coffee/Tea maker, Toaster & Electric Kettles

-Fully equipped kitchen, including pots & pans, tumblers, mugs, and dining set.

-Super awesome Star Wars dining utensils. Don't forget to have your breakfast in the C3PO and R2D2 bowls! 



BEDROOM
- Posture-pedic Queen size bed with quality bed-linen

- Awesome Star Wars memorabilias, including BB-8 and Millenium Falcon bedside lamp.

- When you enter the bedroom, you will be welcomed by Wampa, the snow monster that captured Luke Skywalker in Hoth. Wampa can sleep in the cupboard at night.

- Block out blinds to prevent sun glare from waking you up too early

- Massive wardrobe to fit all your clothes and costumes!


BATHROOM
- Rainmaker head shower & detachable hand-held shower, with complimentary body wash, shampoo, conditioner, and liquid hand soap.

- Nice fluffy towels and hair dryer to help you dry off. 

- Toilet paper

- Look behind the bathroom door, you will find a surprise!



LAUNDRY
- Washing Machine & Dryer so you'll never run out of clean clothes

- Laundry powder (1 wash)

- Iron & Ironing board, don't step out in a creased shirt!

The whole Star Wars themed apartment is yours to enjoy on your own with complete privacy. We offer a simple check-in process so that you can arrive any time after the official check-in time of 3PM. 

The apartment building has a common shared rooftop herb garden which guests can access.

Portable cot and high chairs for your little one are available on request, for $15/day and capped at $50/stay. Please let us know in advance if you will be needing them.

BEFORE ARRIVAL:
We will send you all the information that you will need to ensure a smooth arrival and self check-in process. Please do not hesitate to ask us any question you have. 

AFTER ARRIVAL:
Once you've arrived, you will find clear and comprehensive information on the apartment within the HOUSE MANUAL on the desk. You will also find various books and local map with suggestions for cafes, shops, and local attractions. 
 
We will usually message our guests after arrival to check if they needed anything, and we are always more than happy to provide recommendations. 

MEETING WITH HOST:
As I am working full time and travelling for work a lot, I do not usually meet my guests. 
However, when I am in town, I will be living in the same building... so we might bump into each other in the lift... If you recognise me, please say hi!! I don't bite.. lol...

ISSUES:
If a problem arise, please contact me via AirBnB. My co-host and I are very fast in responding, and we will always try to resolve any issue as soon as possible.

Get the perfect mix of quiet residential life and the convenience of city life when you stay here. North Melbourne has breakfast cafes and boutique shops to enjoy close by, or drive just five minutes to the heart of the Central Business District.

- The apartment is 20mins taxi/uber ride from the Melbourne Airport. 

- Or you can take the Skybus to Southern Cross Station, and catch an uber to the apartment (Uber will cost around $6)

- Nearest tram stop is only 1 block away. Catch tram no. 57 from Errol St or Victoria St to go to the city. 

- Or you can enjoy a short 5-10 minute walk to Elizabeth St.

- Queen Victoria Market is only 5-10 minutes away by foot, where you can find lots of fun shopping and eateries...

- Visit the nearby Lygon St for an authentic Italian dining experience...

- FREE PARKING is available throughout your stay for 1 car. Affordable street-parking available in front of the apartment building.

DISCOUNTS:
Please note we do not offer additional discounts above those already provided for weekly stays. 
Our Star Wars AirBnB is competitively priced, and we take pride into offering an excellent, fun and unique experience to all our guests. We are not merely offering a clean place to sleep.


A FEW RULES:
- Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

- NO SHOES in the apartment/bedroom. Please take your shoes off at the entrance, and place them on the provided shoe rack. 

- DO NOT TOUCH  or MOVE the life size statues

- Do NOT touch the LEGO and the Metal Models

- Star Wars mug and bowls are hand-wash only and non- microwaveable!

- Whilst I encourage you to have fun with the board games and light sabres provided, please be mindful of the neighbours and keep the noise to a minimum level after hours. 

- Do not take any prop out of the apartment. 

- Whilst the apartment is children friendly, please do ask your children to be gentle with the toys. 

- Please immediately inform us if any damage occurred. Excessive cleaning and/or any damage to items in the apartment will result in payment request to guests. 

- STRICTLY NO PARTIES!

All my memorabilia are very precious to me and sourced either during my holidays in the USA and are part of my personal collection. Please do treat them with care like you would your own. Any breakage will result in bond deduction or more.
table.directions:
Meet-up Key Delivery

Our staff will meet you at the apartment.  

Your apartment is located in the back building. When you enter the apartment from the street, go pass the first corridor, out the first building and across the courtyard. You will need to swipe your key again to enter the second building. 

CARPARK ACCESS
The apartment comes with a FREE secure carpark within the premise. 
Carpark entrance is located to the left of the building (when you're standing facing the building). 
Once you have obtained your keys, drive your car to the carpark entrance, and use the black carpark remote to open the gate (press button 1). The gate will automatically close behind you. 
Park in the space marked as "B1-16".

There are also ample of on-street parking space in the area. 

The closest tram stop is on Errol St, with tram 57 taking you to the CBD via Victoria St, Elizabeth St, and Queen Victoria Market.

table.neighborhood_overview: Get the perfect mix of quiet residential life and the convenience of city life when you stay here. North Melbourne has breakfast cafes and boutique shops to enjoy close by, or drive just five minutes to the heart of the Central Business District.
table.notes:
DISCOUNTS:
Please note we do not offer additional discounts above those already provided for weekly stays. 
Our Star Wars AirBnB is competitively priced, and we take pride into offering an excellent, fun and unique experience to all our guests. We are not merely offering a clean place to sleep.


A FEW RULES:
- Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

- NO SHOES in the apartment/bedroom. Please take your shoes off at the entrance, and place them on the provided shoe rack. 

- DO NOT TOUCH  or MOVE the life size statues

- Do NOT touch the LEGO and the Metal Models

- Star Wars mug and bowls are hand-wash only and non- microwaveable!

- Whilst I encourage you to have fun with the board games and light sabres provided, please be mindful of the neighbours and keep the noise to a minimum level after hours. 

- Do not take any prop out of the apartment. 

- Whilst the apartment is children friendly, please do ask your children to be gentle with the toys. 

- Please immediately inform us if any damage occurred. Excessive cleaning and/or any damage to items in the apartment will result in payment request to guests. 

- STRICTLY NO PARTIES!

All my memorabilia are very precious to me and sourced either during my holidays in the USA and are part of my personal collection. Please do treat them with care like you would your own. Any breakage will result in bond deduction or more.

table.space:
1 Bedroom, 1 SofaBed, 1 Bathroom, 1 Carpark

Sleeps 4

Don’t have an AirBnB account? Use this link to receive a credit off your first stay: www.airbnb.com.au/r/marinit1

Welcome to the StarWarsBnB – the first and only Star Wars inspired AirBnB in Australia, located in North Melbourne, approximately 5 minutes from Melbourne CBD. 
Stay in a true Star Wars fan's home featuring original, vintage and new memorabilia from George Lucas’ famous movie series.  

FREE PARKING on the premise is available throughout your stay (1 car).


LIVING ROOM
- Spacious and modern with pull out 3-seater sofa bed that sleeps 2 people.

- Super fast unlimited NBN Wi-Fi for minimal to no buffering time during Netflix!

- 46" Smart HDTV connected to Apple TV & Blu Ray Player, so you can stream all the latest movies and re-watch all the Star Wars sequels.

- Han Solo Bar Fridge

- Vintage Life Size R2D2 and C3P0 to welcome you as soon as you step into the apartment

- SUPER AWESOME lightsabers & voice changing masks for your Jedi-training

- Retro CANDY VENDING MACHINE will bring you back to your childhood

- SEGA Star Projector makes you feel like you are sleeping under the stars

- North facing window allowing ample of natural light into the apartment

- Block out blinds so you can sleep in til late even on the sofa bed.

- Spacious working space for business travellers.

- Quiet & Cozy balcony looking out to a central courtyard filled with lush greeneries, a perfect breakfast spot!

- Board Games for family fun time

- AND many other AMAZING Star Wars gears and toys that you can play with or admire



KITCHEN
-A pantry fully stocked with a range of breakfast items, tea & coffee to help you start your day. 

-French Press Coffee/Tea maker, Toaster & Electric Kettles

-Fully equipped kitchen, including pots & pans, tumblers, mugs, and dining set.

-Super awesome Star Wars dining utensils. Don't forget to have your breakfast in the C3PO and R2D2 bowls! 



BEDROOM
- Posture-pedic Queen size bed with quality bed-linen

- Awesome Star Wars memorabilias, including BB-8 and Millenium Falcon bedside lamp.

- When you enter the bedroom, you will be welcomed by Wampa, the snow monster that captured Luke Skywalker in Hoth. Wampa can sleep in the cupboard at night.

- Block out blinds to prevent sun glare from waking you up too early

- Massive wardrobe to fit all your clothes and costumes!


BATHROOM
- Rainmaker head shower & detachable hand-held shower, with complimentary body wash, shampoo, conditioner, and liquid hand soap.

- Nice fluffy towels and hair dryer to help you dry off. 

- Toilet paper

- Look behind the bathroom door, you will find a surprise!



LAUNDRY
- Washing Machine & Dryer so you'll never run out of clean clothes

- Laundry powder (1 wash)

- Iron & Ironing board, don't step out in a creased shirt!
table.summary:
YESS! THIS IS THE STAR WARS inspired AIRBNB YOU SEE ON THE NEWS

Reviews from our past guests:

★"Just brilliant you must experience for yourself!!"
★"Fantastic Star Wars inspired apartment, wonderfully clean and walking distance to Melbourne CBD"
★"Simply the best AirBnB I have ever stayed in!"
★"Amazing from start to finish. We will be back."
★"Very clean, the bed is super comfy & the place over all is a 10/10"
★"All my friends were jealous"
★"Such a unique apartment in a great part of town"
table.transit:
- The apartment is 20mins taxi/uber ride from the Melbourne Airport. 

- Or you can take the Skybus to Southern Cross Station, and catch an uber to the apartment (Uber will cost around $6)

- Nearest tram stop is only 1 block away. Catch tram no. 57 from Errol St or Victoria St to go to the city. 

- Or you can enjoy a short 5-10 minute walk to Elizabeth St.

- Queen Victoria Market is only 5-10 minutes away by foot, where you can find lots of fun shopping and eateries...

- Visit the nearby Lygon St for an authentic Italian dining experience...

- FREE PARKING is available throughout your stay for 1 car. Affordable street-parking available in front of the apartment building.
