table.access:
Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).
table.description:
With Melbourne's iconic city and Queen Victoria Market minutes from your doorstep, this studio apartment is perfect for travellers who want to explore the hundreds of shops and restaurants in the most liveable city in Australia. With easy access by trams into and around the city, find yourself located in a prime location and in this wonderful and beautiful home that is equipped with everything you need for a comfortable and lovely stay.

This studio apartment contains a comfortable single bed with fresh, clean luxury linens and an all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. There is also sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes. The cosy studio is also furnished with a sofa, coffee table, flat screen TV, and a 2-seater dining table for meals. There is a heating and air-conditioning unit in the living room, but please switch it off when not in use - we deeply appreciate it!

Upon arrival, you will find the BATHROOM stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels, as well as a hair dryer, iron, washing machine and dryer available for your use.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as a kettle, microwave, stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery and dining ware.

Free WIFI is available in the apartment throughout your stay. Please find the WI-FI details in the manual provided to you.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

This apartment is centrally located in the heart of Melbourne CBD and the city's iconic and brimming cultural hub is right at its doorstep.  Many of the city's unique attractions are within walking distance from the Queen Victoria Market to the State Library to Chinatown.  Guests will be spoilt for choice for restaurants, education and retail precincts to visit in this superbly located apartment.

Located near a tram stop just outside the building, along with the city's Free Tram Zone just a block away, guests will have immediate and convenient access to the sprawling Melbourne grid. The Free Tram Zone traverses from Queen Victoria Market, to Docklands' waterfront and everywhere in between. Transportation here is as easy as it gets.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

table.description:
Located on the iconic Flinders Street, this cosy Melbourne-themed apartment truly is in the heart of Melbourne CBD. Just a short walk away from Flinders Street Station, Sea Life Aquarium and Federation Square, this historical building is only a stones throw away from tourist attractions, Melbourne's best restaurants and is just by the Yarra River. Stay here and you'll have this melting-pot of a city at your fingertips.

The BEDROOMS come with luxury linens and quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. Both bedrooms are fitted with a queen sized bed and. ALL bedrooms come with high quality mattresses, comfortable bedding and sufficient storage space for your belongings and clothes. Upon arrival, you will also find the BATHROOMS stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo, conditioner, toilet paper and fresh bath towels. A washing machine and dryer is also available.

The LIVING ROOM contains a 3 seater fabric sofa, fabric armchair, 4 seater dining set and a big flat screen TV. This apartment is furnished with Melbourne themed pictures showcasing what makes Melbourne, Melbourne.

This is perfectly paired with the open-concept KITCHEN within the living room, that is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, microwave, oven, toaster, cutlery, and diningware for you and your group to cook up a delicious meal.

Guests will have access to the entire apartment.

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located in the heart of Melbourne's bustling CBD, this apartment is the epitome of convenience. Surrounded by Melbourne's iconic attractions, such as Block Arcade, Bourke Street Mall, St Paul's Cathedral and Melbourne's famous restaurants, bars and cafes, you'll find yourself spoilt for choice!

This city apartment is located near a multitude of public transport. Located in the Free Tram Zone, you can easily catch a tram on Elizabeth Street or take a train from Flinders St Railway Station. Getting around will be a breeze!

Check-ins after 6pm may incur a late check-in fee.

STRICT HOUSE RULES

-No smoking -No parties -No pets -Maximum number of guests is shown on the listing, please do not have more guests without notifying us. Please keep the apartment in a similar condition as it was during check-in. Breakages, damages, theft and losses will be the guests responsibility. Rules broken will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.

WE WILL CHARGE A $500 FINE FOR SMOKING IN THE APARTMENT.

Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage.

-No eating in the bedrooms
-Correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking
-Check-out by 10 am
-LATE CHECK-IN/CHECK-OUT WILL EACH INCUR A FEE OF $100
-Noise levels to be kept at an appropriate level at all times
-PLEASE USE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the fire alarm. If fire alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily.
-To ensure smooth check-in, we may request additional ID verification from you.
Late check-in fees may apply - $25 for after 9 pm check-in & $50 for after 12midnight check-in
-We provide adequate toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping
- Please note that windows in living area are frosted over
- There are no windows in the bedroom
